{"title": "Ukraine forces complete Patriot air defence training in US", "tags": "world", "timestamp": "2023-03-31", "content": "WASHINGTON \u2013 A group of 65 Ukrainian military personnel has completed training in the United States on the Patriot air defence system and returned to Europe, the Pentagon said on Thursday.\nUkraine had repeatedly pushed the United States for the high-tech system to help shield against Russian strikes and Washington promised in late 2022 that it would provide a Patriot battery, with Kyiv\u2019s troops starting training in Oklahoma in January.\n\u201cThis week, 65 Ukrainian air defenders completed Patriot training at Fort Sill, Oklahoma, and have now arrived back in Europe,\u201d Pentagon spokesman Pat Ryder told journalists.\n\u201cThey\u2019re integrating with other Ukrainian air defenders along with donated Patriot air defence equipment from the United States, Germany and the Netherlands,\u201d he said.\nMore than 7,000 Ukrainian military personnel have been trained by the US since Russia invaded its smaller neighbour in February 2022, Brigadier-General Ryder said.\nMade by Raytheon, the MIM-104 Patriot is a surface-to-air missile system initially developed to intercept high-flying aircraft.\nIt was modified in the 1980s to focus on the new threat of tactical ballistic missiles, and was used in combat against Iraq\u2019s Russian-made Scuds in the first Gulf War. AFP"}